        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT386-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">piriviṭai vaṟpuṟuttun tōḻikkuk kiḻatti vaṉpoṟaiyetir aḻintatu </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken when being desolate in the face of
                    encouragement by HER to the confidante, who encourages [her] in the time of
                    separation. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT386">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> veṇmaṇal virinta vītatai kāṉaṟ</l>
                    <l> ṟaṇṇan tuṟaivaṉ ṟaṇavā vūṅkē</l>
                    <l> vāliḻai makaḷir viḻavaṇi kūṭṭu</l>
                    <l> mālaiyō vaṟivēṉ maṉṉē mālai</l>
                    <l> nilamparan taṉṉa puṉkaṇoṭum</l>
                    <l> pulampuṭait tākuta laṟiyēṉ yāṉē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l rend="indent"> Before the man from the cool ghat, by the seashore grove</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> full of blossoms spread out in the white sand, departed,</l>
                    <l> as for evenings ,</l>
                    <l> when women with pure jewels put together festive ornaments,</l>
                    <l rend="indent6"> I would certainly know [them].</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> That evening possesses loneliness along with sorrow</l>
                    <l> as if to cover the [very] earth I didn't know.</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
